                    <item>
              <title>Contextual challenges in Desktop Computer Basics course</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/7544</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/7544</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p>Our organization, Free Geek Twin Cities, offers free or discounted computers in return for public service. We also hope to provide competencies in computer hardware basics and in the use of free open source software.</p>
<h2>Challenges</h2>
<h3 style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Cultural&nbsp;</h3>
<p style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Female immigrant from East Africa is Muslim and is reluctant to socialize with male strangers. English is her second language and is a barrier to understanding.</p>
<p style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Chemically dependant males sentenced to a half-way house come in to earn a free computer but cannot resist stealing laptops when given the opportunity.</p>
<p style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Ten year olds come in after school and wants to earn a free computer but emotionally immaturity results in adult volunteers not wanting to babysit (discipline)</p>
<h3 style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Mental</h3>
<p style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->A dozen students with Autism Spectrum disorders come in to learn job skills</p>
<p style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Individules with&nbsp;Attention deficit-hyperactivity disorder (ADHD) wish to earn computers and learn job skills.</p>
<h3 style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Motivational</h3>
<p style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Individule is sentenced to serve and wishes to work 120 hrs as an alternative to 6 months in prison. She does not give the required hours but edits our tracking data base and prints out a copy for proof of compliance for her hearing.</p>
<p style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Seven ex-prisoners are given early release to a half-way house. A grant proposal offers to pay them $8/hr for 50 hrs if we can provide supervised work for them.</p>
<h3 style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Physical</h3>
<p style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Three of our volunteers have been in wheelchairs and one was a quadriplegic, only able to talk and to point with a baton held in his mouth.</p>
<p style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->One woman volunteer is legally blind.</p>
<h3 style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Environmental</h3>
<p style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Learner has an allergic reaction to mold in room</p>
<p style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->learners are too cold or too hot</p>
<p style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->learner can't stand the choice of music being played</p>
<p style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Too much noise from environment is distracting</p>]]></description>
          <pubDate>Thu, 17 Jan 2013 19:31:35 +0000</pubDate>
            </item>
                    <item>
              <title>Desktop Computer Basics - a course design</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/7534</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/7534</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p>I hope to <strong>design a learning activity</strong> that will result in&nbsp;the participant being able to</p>
<ul>
<li>connect a mouse, keyboard, and monitor to a desktop computer</li>
<li>connect the computer to a power source and turn it on</li>
<li>disassemble the computer into its component parts and put it back together again</li>
<li>be able to name the parts of the computer and what they do</li>
<li>be able to install an operating system &#40;OS: Linux Xubuntu&#41; from an install CD</li>
<li>be able to update, personalize, customise, and add extras to their OS</li>
</ul>
<p>The learning design should allow learning with minimal supervision.</p>]]></description>
          <pubDate>Thu, 17 Jan 2013 17:06:36 +0000</pubDate>
